532908.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAmyotrophic%20lateral%20sclerosis%20(ALS)%2C%20or%20Lou%20Gehrig's%20disease%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20brutal%20diseases%20out%20there.%20Per%20Mayo%20Clinic%2C%20it%20is%20a%20progressive%2C%20fatal%20neurodegenerative%20disease%20that%20slowly%20destroys%20motor%20neurons%20controlling%20voluntary%20muscles.%20It%20causes%20muscle%20weakness%2C%20twitching%2C%20and%20paralysis%2C%20and%20typically%20leads%20to%20respiratory%20failure%20within%203%E2%80%935%20years.%20Despite%20decades%20of%20research%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20cure%20yet.%20The%20only%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20to%20manage%20the%20symptoms.Even%20with%20that%2C%20for%20most%20people%2C%20the%20fight%20is%20short%20and%20tough.Hollywood%20just%20lost%20one%20of%20the%20most%20well-known%20faces%2C%20Eric%20Dane%2C%20to%20this%20disease.%20The%20world%20knows%20him%20as%20Dr.%20Mark%20Sloan%2C%20aka%20%E2%80%9CMcSteamy%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%98Grey%E2%80%99s%20Anatomy%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20from%20%E2%80%98Euphoria%E2%80%99.%20He%20passed%20away%20in%20February%202026%20after%20his%20own%20battle%20with%20ALS.Dane%20isn%E2%80%99t%20alone%3B%20some%20familiar%20faces%20from%20Hollywood%20have%20fought%20their%20own%20battles%20with%20ALS.%20Quite%20a%20few%20of%20them%20have%20shared%20their%20journey%20publicly%20in%20order%20to%20raise%20awareness%20about%20the%20disease.%20With%20their%20courage%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20share%20such%20a%20personal%20experience%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20also%20pushed%20the%20conversation%20forward%20about%20why%20we%20need%20more%20research%20and%20better%20support%20for%20people%20living%20with%20it.Here%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20take%20a%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20Hollywood%20names%20we%E2%80%99ve%20lost%20to%20ALS%2C%20and%20how%20they%20made%20their%20mark.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773533586000%2C%22image%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-129532908%2Cimgsize-54356.cms%22%2C%22url%22%3A%22http